```csharp
using System;
using System.Runtime.InteropServices;

public static class NativeCompression
{
    [DllImport("compresslib", CallingConvention = CallingConvention.Cdecl, ExactSpelling = true)]
    public static extern int compress_buffer(
        [In] byte[] input,
        UIntPtr input_len,
        [Out] byte[] output,
        UIntPtr output_len,
        out UIntPtr bytes_written);
}
```

Key choices:

- **`UIntPtr`** for `size_t` — maps correctly to 4 bytes on x86 (and scales on x64).
- **`CallingConvention.Cdecl`** — the C function has no `__stdcall` annotation.
- **`[In]`/`[Out]`** attributes — hints the marshaller to avoid unnecessary copies.
- **`out UIntPtr`** for the `size_t*` parameter — passes a pointer the callee writes to.
